<p>Given the similarity in average annual sale volumes between these two sets of managers, it becomes apparent that the volume of trading has limited influence on the alpha performance of managers, as per the findings of this study. It is worth noting that both active and less active managers, in terms of trading activities, are well represented in both the upper and lower segments of manager performance.</p>
